# Phase 3 — Reporting & Analytics

> **Priority:** 🔴 High | **Effort:** ~5–6 weeks | **Dependencies:** All existing modules (data sources), Exams (Phase 1)

## Why This Is #3

Data is already being collected across 12 modules but there's no unified lens to view it. Principals and managers make decisions based on reports. This module turns raw data into **actionable insights**.

---

## Scope

### 3.1 Student Performance Analytics
- **Subject-wise analysis** — Average, highest, lowest, distribution histogram
- **Trend analysis** — Student's performance across exams over time (line chart)
- **Class comparison** — Compare average performance across sections/classes
- **At-risk students** — Flag students scoring below threshold consistently
- **Topper board** — Per exam, per subject, overall

### 3.2 Financial Reports
- **Daily collection report** — All payments received today with breakdowns
- **Fee collection summary** — By class, fee type, date range, payment mode
- **Outstanding dues report** — Students with pending fees, aging analysis (30/60/90 days)
- **Revenue trend** — Monthly/yearly revenue trend charts
- **Fee type analysis** — Which fee types contribute most revenue
- **Concession/waiver report** — Total concessions granted, by category
- **Receipt register** — Sequential receipt log

### 3.3 Attendance Analytics
- **Daily summary** — Present/absent/late counts per class
- **Monthly attendance percentage** — Per student, per class
- **Chronic absenteeism** — Students below X% threshold flagged
- **Subject-wise attendance** (if subject-level tracking enabled)
- **Teacher attendance** (links to HR in Phase 5)
- **Trend chart** — Attendance % over months

### 3.4 Admission Analytics
- **Application pipeline** — Funnel: Applied → Verified → Selected → Enrolled
- **Source analysis** — Where applicants hear about the institution
- **Conversion rate** — Applications to admissions %
- **Seat fill rate** — Seats filled vs capacity per stream/class
- **Year-over-year comparison**

### 3.5 Library & Inventory Reports
- **Library** — Most borrowed books, overdue trends, genre popularity
- **Inventory** — Stock valuation, movement trends, low-stock alerts, sales analysis

### 3.6 Custom Report Builder (Phase 3b — deferred slightly)
- Drag-and-drop field selector from available entity fields
- Filter, group by, sort
- Save as named report template
- Schedule automatic email delivery (weekly/monthly)

### 3.7 Universal Export
- Every report exportable to **PDF** and **Excel**
- Print-optimized layouts
- Bulk export (e.g., all student report cards as a single PDF)

